00:04:42.895 --> 00:04:47.405
so we can replace the bit in parentheses with one over the focal length.

84
00:04:47.405 --> 00:04:54.345
So, the optical path length of a paraxial thin lens is minus R squared over 2f.

85
00:04:54.345 --> 00:04:55.715
That's an important expression,

